RIGHT function

+-----------------------------------------------------------------------------+
| RIGHT(string, length, [pad])                                                |
+-----------------------------------------------------------------------------+

Returns a string composed of the rightmost length characters of the string,
extended on the left with the pad character as necessary.

Examples:

    RIGHT('abc  d',8)  == '  abc  d'
    RIGHT('abc def',5) == 'c def'
    RIGHT('12',5,0)    == '00012'
